Name Rascal/Expressions/Values/Value/NotEqual

Syntax Exp1 != Exp2
Types
Exp1 Exp2 Exp1 != Exp2
value value bool
Description Yields true if both arguments are not identical and false otherwise.
Examples 

  Introduce two variables X, Y and Z and force them to be of type value:


rascal>value X = "abc";
value: "abc"
rascal>value Y = "abc";
value: "abc"
rascal>value Z = 3.14;
value: 3.14


  Now compare X and Y for inequality:


rascal>X != Y;
bool: false


  and X and Z:


rascal>X != Z;
bool: true
